fields.name: Apricot Globemallow
fields.description: This drought-resistant plant is well-suited for semi-arid areas in Kenya like Turkana and Kitui. Itâ€™s known for its vibrant apricot-colored flowers.

fields.name: Cone Peak Bedstraw
fields.description: A hardy plant found in the highlands of Kenya such as Nyeri and Meru. It is popular for its medicinal properties and resilience in cold climates.

fields.name: Blutaparon
fields.description: Blutaparon thrives in coastal regions like Mombasa and Lamu, making it a good choice for sandy soils and salty conditions.

fields.name: Chamisso Sedge
fields.description: This grass-like plant is commonly found in wetlands and marshy areas like Naivasha and Lake Victoria regions. It helps prevent soil erosion.

fields.name: Marsh Straw Sedge
fields.description: Ideal for regions like the Kisii highlands, this plant grows in swampy and moist conditions, often used for mat weaving.

fields.name: Largeflower False Rosemary
fields.description: Found in hilly terrains like Kericho and Nandi, this plant is admired for its aromatic properties and large flowers.

fields.name: Oregon Bleeding Heart
fields.description: This stunning plant is suitable for decorative gardens in urban centers like Nairobi and Kisumu due to its heart-shaped flowers.

fields.name: Pore Lichen
fields.description: Commonly found on rocks and tree trunks in forested areas like Kakamega Forest, this lichen is used for dyeing and traditional medicine.

fields.name: Chinese Haw
fields.description: An exotic plant that grows well in Kenyan highlands and is known for its small, edible berries with a sweet-tart flavor.

fields.name: Toringo Crab
fields.description: A unique plant with crabapple-like fruits, thriving in regions like Eldoret and Nakuru due to favorable conditions.

fields.name: Kauai Hau Kuahiwi
fields.description: Native to tropical climates, this plant is suitable for coastal and lowland areas like Kwale.

fields.name: Pygmy Goldenweed
fields.description: A small, resilient plant commonly found in semi-arid regions like Garissa. Known for its golden-yellow blooms.

fields.name: Red-vein Yellow Loosestrife
fields.description: This vibrant plant with red veins and yellow flowers is commonly found in wetlands and near rivers like Athi and Tana.

fields.name: Isachne
fields.description: A grass species found in the tea-growing regions of Kenya like Kericho and Nandi Hills, used for erosion control.

fields.name: Santo Domingo False Willow
fields.description: Suitable for areas like Kitale and Bungoma, this willow-like plant provides shade and soil conservation benefits.
